snippet: Two leaders of Femen, the women’s rights group known for staging bare-breasted political protests, were assaulted while on vacation in the Black Sea port city of Odessa.
abstract: Leaders of Femen, Ukrainian women's rights group known for staging bare-breasted political protests, demand government protection after two of them, Anna Hutsol and Alexandra Shevchenko, and male associate are assaulted while on vacation in Black Sea port city of Odessa.
lead_paragraph: Two leaders of Femen, the women’s rights group known for staging bare-breasted political protests, were assaulted while on vacation in the Black Sea port city of Odessa.

headline.main: Feminists Ask for Protection After Attack in Ukraine
headline.print_headline: Feminist Group Seeks Protection in Ukraine
